FT Excess Deaths Updated with Israel

Ariel Karlinsky

18 8 2020

Preface

Load FT data on excess deaths, update with Israel and maybe even send a push request to FT.

ft_data <- read_csv("data/ft_excess_deaths.csv")

Add to ft_data the total excess deaths in each country in 2020:

ft_total_excess_deaths <- ft_data %>%
  filter(country == region) %>%
  filter(year == 2020) %>%
  group_by(country) %>%
  arrange(country, week) %>%
  mutate(total_excess_deaths = cumsum(excess_deaths)) %>%
  group_by(country) %>%
  slice_tail(n = 1)

Plot:

ft_data %>%
  filter(country == region) %>%
  filter(year >= 2015) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = week, y = deaths, group = factor(year))) +
  geom_line(alpha = 0.5) +
  geom_line(data = . %>% filter(year == 2020), color = "firebrick1") +
  labs(title = "Excess deaths by country, week and year",
       subtitle = "Red line is 2020 \nGrey lines are 2015 to 2019 \nBlack line is historical median", y = "Excess deaths", x = "Week",
       caption = "Source: FT Data on Excess Mortality") +
  lemon::facet_rep_wrap(~country, scales = "free_y", repeat.tick.labels = TRUE)

Load updated data for Israel, weekly and monthly:

israel_deaths_weekly <- read_excel("Data/Deaths.xlsx", sheet = "weekly")

israel_deaths_weekly %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = starts_with("deaths"), names_to = c("type","year"), 
               values_to = "deaths", names_sep = "_") %>%
  select(-type) %>%
  mutate(country = "Israel (Updated)",
         region = "Israel (Updated)") %>%
  group_by(week) %>%
  mutate(expected_deaths = median(deaths[year != 2020])) %>%
  arrange(year, week) %>%
  mutate(excess_deaths = deaths - expected_deaths,
         year = as.integer(year)) -> israel_deaths_weekly_forMerge

Appending Israel data to FT data

ft_data %>%
  bind_rows(israel_deaths_weekly_forMerge) -> ft_data_updated

Add to updated FT data excess deaths:

ft_updated_total_excess_deaths <- ft_data_updated %>%
  filter(country == region) %>%
  filter(year == 2020) %>%
  filter(!is.na(deaths)) %>%
  group_by(country) %>%
  arrange(country, week) %>%
  mutate(total_excess_deaths = cumsum(excess_deaths)) %>%
  group_by(country) %>%
  slice_tail(n = 1)

Plot updated

ft_data_updated %>%
  filter(country == region) %>%
  filter(year >= 2015) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = week, y = deaths, group = factor(year))) +
  geom_line(alpha = 0.5) +
  geom_line(aes(y = expected_deaths)) +
  geom_line(data = . %>% filter(year == 2020), color = "firebrick1") +
    labs(title = "Excess deaths by country, week and year",
       subtitle = "Red line is 2020 \nGrey lines are 2015 to 2019 \nBlack line is historical median", y = "Excess deaths", x = "Week",
       caption = "Source: FT Data on Excess Mortality Updated with CBS data") +
  lemon::facet_rep_wrap(~country, scales = "free_y", repeat.tick.labels = TRUE)

# Total Excess Deaths by last week of reporting

g1 <- ft_updated_total_excess_deaths %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=reorder(country,total_excess_deaths), 
             y=total_excess_deaths,
             label = scales::comma(total_excess_deaths, accuracy = 1))) +
  geom_col(fill = "firebrick1") +
  geom_text(size = 3, color = "firebrick1", hjust = -0.2) +
  coord_flip() +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::comma_format(accuracy = 1),
                     expand = expansion(mult = c(0.15,0.15))) +
  labs(title = "Total excess deaths in 2020 by country",
       y = "Total excess deaths",
       x = NULL,
       subtitle = "End week varies by country",
       caption = "Source: FT data, updated with Israeli data from CBS") +
  theme(panel.grid.major.y  = element_blank())

g1

Last week of reporting by country:

g2 <- ft_updated_total_excess_deaths %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=reorder(country,total_excess_deaths), 
             y=week,
             label = week)) +
  geom_col(fill = "firebrick1") +
  geom_text(size = 3, color = "firebrick1", hjust = -0.2) +
  coord_flip() +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::comma_format(accuracy = 1),
                     expand = expansion(mult = c(0,0.15))) +
  labs(title = "Last week of reporting deaths by country",
       y = "Last week",
       x = NULL,
       subtitle = "End week varies by country",
       caption = "Source: FT data, updated with Israeli data from CBS") +
  theme(panel.grid.major.y  = element_blank())

g2

Put together:

g1 + g2
